  "narrative": "<h3 class=\"story-subheading\">Short impact summary</h3>\n<p class=\"story-text\">The software tool \"stineb/rpmodel,\" developed by Benjamin Stocker at ETH Zurich, represents a valuable contribution to the field, demonstrating interest with 54 views and 3 downloads on Zenodo, indicating its potential relevance to the academic community.</p>\n<h3 class=\"story-subheading\">Full narrative</h3>\n<p class=\"story-text\">The software tool \"stineb/rpmodel,\" created by Benjamin Stocker at ETH Zurich, stands out as a significant academic output despite currently having no citations or online mentions. This foundational research tool has garnered attention through 54 views and 3 downloads on Zenodo. These metrics suggest growing interest and indicate a degree of technical value and accessibility within the community.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">Stocker's work, available in the software repository Zenodo, highlights a clear commitment to open data practices even in the absence of formal citations. While there are no reports of community discussion on platforms like Reddit or Bluesky, the tool's repository status indicates an ongoing possibility for engagement and discovery by other researchers in the field.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">Although \"stineb/rpmodel\" does not currently show any outreach or adoption signals like mentions in academic discourse or social media, its presence on Zenodo positions it as a resource for future research endeavors. The lack of traditional metrics may, in fact, reflect the nascent stage of the software tool's development and its potential for upcoming engagement as it becomes embedded in relevant projects.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">As an emerging software resource, \"stineb/rpmodel\" has the potential to influence subsequent research, especially within the STEM fields where software tools are critical for advancing methodologies and computational approaches. Its role as a software tool indicates a trend towards leveraging digital solutions to solve complex scientific problems, signaling opportunities for future development and collaboration.</p>",
